1.title: Want to Bet, Jennie?

episode of.title: Jennie Garth: A Little Bit Country (TV Series 2012– )

1.plot: Jennie throws Carolyn (Jennie's Mother) and Gary (Carolyn's new husband) a "Welcome Home from Your Honeymoon BBQ". A bluegrass band, a mechanical bull and twinkle lights adorn the side yard.

2.title: A Star Is Born

episode of.title: Jennie Garth: A Little Bit Country (TV Series 2012– )

2.plot: Jennie helps Luca, her 14-year-old daughter, start a career as a singer/songwriter after Corinne books Luca's first live music show at an old folks home.

3.title: Puppy Love

episode of.title: Jennie Garth: A Little Bit Country (TV Series 2012– )

3.plot: Jennie is looking to get back to her country roots by moving her family to a bucolic seven-acre farm in the Central California countryside.

4.title: Love Retreat

episode of.title: Jennie Garth: A Little Bit Country (TV Series 2012– )

4.plot: Jennie, her friend Adelle and Corinne go on a road trip up the beautiful Pacific Coast Highway landing in Big Sur, California. The trio attends an Oceanside "Love Retreat" where they discuss emotional wreckage and marital difficulties.

5.title: Anger Management

episode of.title: Jennie Garth: A Little Bit Country (TV Series 2012– )

5.plot: Jennie and her daughters - Luca, Lola and Fiona - decide to build a treehouse hideaway while Corinne plans activities for Jennie to release anger. Jennie finds solace spending time with her girls sawing, hammering and painting.

imdb.plot outline: Twenty years ago, Jennie Garth moved from Urbana, Illinois to Los Angeles to pursue acting and promptly took the Hollywood world by storm as one of the breakout stars of the monster hit, Beverly Hills, 90210. Now Jennie is in search of a simpler life, as she moves her family to a seven-acre farm in the countryside of Central California, where she hopes to put the pressures of Hollywood aside and experience a new way of life. It's a move that will either give her the all-American lifestyle she has always dreamed of, or turn her family's world completely upside down.
